                        },
                        "displayName": "Rok Mihevc",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Amsterdam"
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah, I think your suggestion is valid. We can use temporal subtract kernel: `subtract(timestamp, subtract(1970-01-01 - origin))`. This is pretty harmless and clean.\r\nHowever maybe there are cases in lubridate where origin of a timestamp changes output of a function? I don't know how common origin is in lubridate, but I see it is in clock where [e.g. flooring uses it|https://clock.r-lib.org/articles/recipes.html#flooring-by-days]. Do we know of such things in lubridate?\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rokm",
                        "name": "rokm",
                        "key": "rokm",
                        "avatarUrls": {
