                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "Pandas also has such an {{origin}} keyword in {{pd.to_datetime}} (I seem to remember that it can, for example, be useful for data coming from Matlab).\r\n\r\nIf we want to add something like this, I think we should add it as a separate kernel (to specifically convert integers/doubles to timestamp or date), and not add this to Cast.",
